<task id="R2-019" project="SprkChat Platform Enhancement R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>DynamicCommandResolver — Metadata-Driven Command Catalog from Playbooks + Scopes with Redis Cache</title>
    <status>pending</status>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, cache, redis</tags>
    <estimated-effort>medium</estimated-effort>
    <parallel-group>B</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>BFF API code implementation — creates DynamicCommandResolver with Redis caching and metadata-driven Dataverse queries; FR-05, FR-17 requirements; no static relationship tables</rigor-reason>
    <dependencies>[001, 006]</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Create a new class `DynamicCommandResolver` in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/`
    (factory-instantiated, NOT DI-registered) that builds a command catalog from metadata-driven
    Dataverse queries with Redis caching.

    **Command catalog entry**:
    ```csharp
    public record CommandEntry(
        string Id,           // slash command identifier, e.g., "search-legal-database"
        string Label,        // display label, e.g., "Search Legal Database"
        string Description,  // tooltip/aria description
        string Trigger,      // the slash command string, e.g., "/search-legal-database"
        string Category,     // "system" | "playbook" | "scope"
        string Source);      // playbookId or scopeId that contributed this command
    ```

    **Three command sources** (no static relationship tables):
    1. **System commands**: hardcoded base set (`/help`, `/clear`, `/export`) — always present
    2. **Playbook commands**: query `sprk_analysisplaybook` filtered by `sprk_recordType = context.RecordType`
       — each playbook's `sprk_triggerPhrases` field provides slash command suggestions
    3. **Scope capability commands**: query active scopes for `sprk_capabilities` values — each
       capability option set value maps to a command entry (see mapping below)

    **Capability → command mapping**:
    - `search` (100000000) → `{ id: "search", label: "Search", trigger: "/search", category: "scope" }`
    - `analyze` (100000001) → `{ id: "analyze", label: "Analyze Document", trigger: "/analyze", category: "scope" }`
    - `web_search` (100000002) → `{ id: "web-search", label: "Search the Web", trigger: "/web-search", category: "scope" }`
    - `write_back` (100000003) → `{ id: "write-back", label: "Write to Document", trigger: "/write-back", category: "scope" }`
    - `summarize` (100000004) → `{ id: "summarize", label: "Summarize", trigger: "/summarize", category: "scope" }`

    **Redis cache**:
    - Cache key: `cmd-catalog:{tenantId}:{recordType}`
    - TTL: 5 minutes
    - On cache miss: query Dataverse, build catalog, cache result
    - On cache hit: return cached result directly

    **Class design**:
    ```csharp
    public class DynamicCommandResolver
    {
        public DynamicCommandResolver(IDataverseRepository dataverse, IDistributedCache cache,
            ILogger&lt;DynamicCommandResolver&gt; logger) { ... }

        public Task&lt;IReadOnlyList&lt;CommandEntry&gt;&gt; ResolveCommandsAsync(ChatHostContext context,
            CancellationToken cancellationToken = default);
    }
    ```

    **NFR-03**: Full resolution must complete within 3 seconds with Redis cache hit.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer with Azure AI and Minimal API expertise</role>

  <goal>
    `DynamicCommandResolver` returns a complete command catalog from three sources (system, playbook,
    scope) with 5-minute Redis cache and tenant-scoped cache keys. Different analysis record types
    show different available commands (FR-05). Adding a new playbook with matching record type makes
    its commands appear in SprkChat without configuration after cache expiry (FR-17).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="Project specification — FR-05, FR-17 (dynamic commands, no static tables), NFR-03 (3s resolution)">projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/spec.md</file>
