    <patterns>
      <pattern>Redis get-or-set pattern: `var cached = await _cache.GetStringAsync(key, ct); if (cached != null) return JsonSerializer.Deserialize&lt;T&gt;(cached); var result = await BuildCatalogAsync(context, ct); await _cache.SetStringAsync(key, JsonSerializer.Serialize(result), options, ct); return result;`</pattern>
      <pattern>Tenant-scoped cache key: extract tenantId from ChatHostContext or HttpContext; use format `cmd-catalog:{tenantId}:{recordType}` to prevent cross-tenant data bleed</pattern>
      <pattern>Dataverse playbook query filter: `$filter=sprk_recordtype eq '{context.RecordType}' and statecode eq 0` — active playbooks only, matching record type</pattern>
      <pattern>Capability option set reading: multi-select field returns as comma-delimited integers in OData response — split and map to CommandEntry records using the fixed mapping table</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      SprkChat R1 had static slash commands hardcoded in the frontend. R2 makes them dynamic: the
      command catalog is assembled at session init from Dataverse metadata. This means:
      - A legal matter session shows `/search-legal-database` (from Legal Research scope's capabilities)
      - A project session shows `/generate-status-report` (from Project playbooks)
      - Both sessions show `/help`, `/clear`, `/export` (system commands)

      No static relationship tables: the connection between "which commands appear for this record type"
      is derived from:
      1. Playbook records filtered by `sprk_recordType`
      2. Scope capability option set values on active scopes

      Redis caching with 5-minute TTL prevents redundant Dataverse queries on every message. The catalog
      is tenant-scoped (not user-scoped) because commands are based on configuration, not user permissions.

      Task R2-021 (ScopeCapabilitiesService) will further refine scope command contribution — this task
      provides the initial implementation that R2-021 will integrate with.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      Depends on Task R2-001 (Dataverse schema with sprk_capabilities field and sprk_recordType field)
      and R2-006 (Phase 1 deployment). Independent of other Group B tasks — safe for parallel execution.
      Task R2-020 (AnalysisChatContextResolver) and R2-021 (ScopeCapabilities) depend on this task's
      output. Own files: `Services/Ai/Chat/DynamicCommandResolver.cs`, `Models/Ai/Chat/CommandEntry.cs`.
    </dependencies>
  </context>

