  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">For a "matter" record type, the command catalog includes commands from playbooks with `sprk_recordType = "matter"` but NOT from "project" playbooks</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">System commands (`/help`, `/clear`, `/export`) appear in every catalog regardless of record type</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">A scope with `sprk_capabilities = [100000002, 100000004]` (web_search, summarize) contributes `/web-search` and `/summarize` to the catalog</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Second call to `ResolveCommandsAsync` with same tenantId+recordType returns result from Redis (cache hit) within 100ms</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Redis cache key follows the pattern `cmd-catalog:{tenantId}:{recordType}` with 5-minute TTL (verify TTL in Redis)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Adding a new playbook with matching recordType causes the new command to appear after cache TTL expiry (no code change needed)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">DynamicCommandResolver is NOT in the DI container (factory instantiation only)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet build` passes with no errors</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The `IDataverseRepository` in this context likely refers to whatever Dataverse access abstraction
    exists in the BFF. Check `AnalysisChatContextResolver.cs` and existing service classes to find the
    correct interface name — it may be `IChatDataverseRepository`, `IDataverseClient`, or similar.
    Use the existing abstraction; do NOT create a new Dataverse access class.

    For converting trigger phrases to slash command slugs: take the first phrase, convert to lowercase,
    replace spaces with hyphens, strip non-alphanumeric characters except hyphens. E.g.,
    "Send analysis by email" → "send-analysis-by-email" → trigger `/send-analysis-by-email`.
    Cap the trigger length at 50 characters.

    The `sprk_triggerPhrases` field is newline-delimited (from Task R2-001). Use only the FIRST phrase
    for the slash command trigger — subsequent phrases are for semantic matching in PlaybookDispatcher,
    not for slash command generation.
  </notes>

